				<outline text="Autonomous cars everywhere?" created="Wed, 25 Aug 2021 16:38:42 GMT" type="outline" metaImage="http://scripting.com/images/2021/08/25/carmess.png" description="I imagined a car plowing into a crowd and killing twenty innocent people because some idiot at Apple decided to change the order of the params...">
					<outline text="I remember a couple of years ago people were confidently saying that by now the streets would be full of autonomous cars. " created="Wed, 25 Aug 2021 16:38:54 GMT"/>
					<outline text="They snickered when people like me who have spent a life programming thought that was a pretty shitty idea. Who would even want to go out for a walk with driverless cars all over the place, subject to programmers' mistakes, or the callous deprecations of platform vendors. " created="Wed, 25 Aug 2021 16:42:34 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I imagined a car plowing into a crowd and killing twenty innocent people because some idiot at Apple decided to change the order the params of an API because they felt like it, and the car software dev missed the notice and didn't update the car's OS. " created="Wed, 25 Aug 2021 16:41:20 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Oh sure I want software doing all the driving after less than two years of a burn in. Yeah that makes all the sense in the world. (Sorry for the sarcasm.)" created="Wed, 25 Aug 2021 16:41:32 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Graduation day, 1976" created="Wed, 25 Aug 2021 13:01:10 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Here I am, in 1976, holding a college diploma. My parents, grandmother and brother came down to New Orleans for the occasion. They were happy because no one expected me to get a college degree. This came from my father's photo scrapbook." created="Wed, 25 Aug 2021 13:01:22 GMT" inlineImage="http://scripting.com/images/2021/08/25/daveGraduationDay.png"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 24" created="Tue, 24 Aug 2021 12:59:01 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="24">
				<outline text="Today's song: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zaKEcCAeSe8&quot;&gt;Undercover of the Night&lt;/a&gt;." created="Tue, 24 Aug 2021 17:23:57 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Am I passionate about the idea of a &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1430150972123254799&quot;&gt;modular newsletter system&lt;/a&gt; so  writers can use the best editor, the one that fits them best, the one they've been using for decades? Yes, I am. I'll keep beating the drum. I won't stop. That's how I am until I get what I want. :smile:" created="Tue, 24 Aug 2021 21:16:37 GMT" type="outline" image="http://scripting.com/images/2019/12/24/drummer.png"/>
				<outline text="When will someone launch a newsletter service that lets you use whatever editor you like. I predict that I will support that product in the new editor I'm working on. I don't want to do a newsletter service myself. Let's get something fun started." created="Tue, 24 Aug 2021 12:59:02 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="What makes a bug report good? It makes it easy for the dev to reproduce the problem. I have to see it myself to understand what the problem is. Your theory on what the problem is, or judgment on whether you followed the instructions is secondary. " created="Tue, 24 Aug 2021 15:14:30 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Unfortunately journalists don't stand for re-election. They are not term-limited. There is no journalism for journalism. Our opinions are not sought. But if we ever do get a chance to vote one of them out in some significant way, I bet a lot of people will line up to do it. I know I will. And I'm not talking about the people on Fox.  " created="Tue, 24 Aug 2021 15:58:57 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Anyone know how to &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1430220866282000394&quot;&gt;enter Cmd-/&lt;/a&gt; on a German keyboard?" created="Tue, 24 Aug 2021 17:36:16 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="NY strong" created="Tue, 24 Aug 2021 15:52:52 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I don't know if these ads are for real." created="Tue, 24 Aug 2021 15:53:09 GMT" inlineImage="http://scripting.com/images/2021/08/24/nycSubwayAds.png"/>
