			<outline text="August 23" created="Mon, 23 Aug 2021 14:15:36 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="23">
				<outline text="I'd say &quot;Bingeworthy&quot; didn't work. &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/images/2021/08/23/bingeworthyScreen.png&quot;&gt;Nice software&lt;/a&gt;, but the goal was to keep an easy to find &lt;a href=&quot;http://my.bingeworthy.io/davewiner/&quot;&gt;public list&lt;/a&gt; of shows I recommend, and those that my friends recommend. A couple of weeks ago I discovered, entirely on my own, &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rick_and_Morty&quot;&gt;Rick and Morty&lt;/a&gt;. I loved it from the first scene in the first epsiode. I started telling everyone I know how great it is, and with few exceptions they said &quot;old news Dave.&quot; They loved the show since it started in &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Rick_and_Morty_episodes#Season_1_(2013%E2%80%9314)&quot;&gt;2013&lt;/a&gt;. Why did I struggle for years to find something great to watch when Rick and Morty was out there. I'm sure there are a dozen other delicious shows I don't know about, and it's only getting worse. What is the answer? It seems like a simple problem to solve, yet it evades an answer.  " created="Mon, 23 Aug 2021 14:17:48 GMT" type="outline" image="http://scripting.com/images/2021/08/07/rickAndMorty.png"/>
				<outline text="They've had the same tired old guests on the cable news shows for years. They always say the same things. How is it that people don't just change channels and tune into 30-year-old Law &amp; Order reruns instead. I've been enjoying watching the reruns for the 15th time. Compared to the news they seem fresh and strangely relevant. " created="Tue, 24 Aug 2021 02:16:40 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="When you check into Twitter after being gone for a while, you see, for an instant, some posts, not sure when they're from, but they might be appealing, but too bad, they disappear just after your mind registers that they're there. Happens regularly." created="Tue, 24 Aug 2021 02:13:46 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="The remains of &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hurricane_Henri&quot;&gt;Tropical Storm Henri&lt;/a&gt; has been parked overhead for about 24 hours. Pouring rain, hour after hour. Not much wind. I couldn't go riding yesterday, and probably won't be able to today either. Tomorrow should be hot and humid, good swimming weather. :smile:" created="Mon, 23 Aug 2021 15:25:02 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Finished &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Schmigadoon!&quot;&gt;Schmigadoon&lt;/a&gt; on Apple. First few episodes were pretty awful, but I'm glad I stuck with it, the last two were gems. I adore &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cecily_Strong&quot;&gt;Cecily Strong&lt;/a&gt;.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kristin_Chenoweth&quot;&gt;Kristin Chenoweth&lt;/a&gt; has the best &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_PmS5JIfSkk&quot;&gt;song&lt;/a&gt;.  " created="Mon, 23 Aug 2021 14:17:25 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Remember how &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.npr.org/2012/09/01/160438753/how-government-became-a-dirty-word&quot;&gt;Reagan said&lt;/a&gt; government is the problem. He was wrong, it's actually journalism. " created="Mon, 23 Aug 2021 14:15:37 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Edward Hopper" created="Tue, 24 Aug 2021 02:44:22 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.wikiart.org/en/edward-hopper/summertime&quot;&gt;Summertime&lt;/a&gt;, 1943." created="Tue, 24 Aug 2021 02:44:26 GMT" inlineImage="http://scripting.com/images/2021/08/23/summertimeHopper1943.png"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 22" created="Sun, 22 Aug 2021 14:28:52 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="22">
				<outline text="Today's song: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TvMS_ykiLiQ&quot;&gt;City of New Orleans&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Mon, 23 Aug 2021 03:08:51 GMT" type="outline" urlvideo="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TvMS_ykiLiQ"/>
				<outline text="You'd think that by now [[Facebook]] would have figured out how to make a &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/images/2021/08/22/squintyText.png&quot;&gt;story&lt;/a&gt; read well on their website, by default, based on who's reading and what their vision is capable of. I can kind of read a &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/images/2021/08/22/squintyText.png&quot;&gt;story&lt;/a&gt; like this, but it involves a lot of squinting and scrolling and interpolating." created="Sun, 22 Aug 2021 17:57:30 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="A perhaps surprising truth. We aren't free to ignore other people. For example, you're not allowed to shit in a public swimming pool. Think about it and all the other things you aren't free to do. It's not something you can argue about and live with other people." created="Sun, 22 Aug 2021 17:13:02 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Extreme silo-osity" created="Mon, 23 Aug 2021 00:22:33 GMT" type="outline" metaImage="http://scripting.com/images/2021/08/22/fishingByManet1863.png" description="Componentize so some devs can specialize in editors and others can specialize in distribution.">
					<outline text="&lt;i&gt;I tried to post this reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/om/status/1429230610439041025&quot;&gt;Om on Twitter&lt;/a&gt; but it wouldn't let me. &lt;/i&gt;" created="Mon, 23 Aug 2021 00:22:48 GMT">
						<outline text="Om, the height of silo-osity was when [[Substack]] came along, they insisted that in order to use their service you had to use their editor. I absolutely refused to do that, so I had to write my own &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/email/&quot;&gt;email distributer app&lt;/a&gt;. What a waste of effort. " created="Mon, 23 Aug 2021 00:22:35 GMT"/>
						<outline text="We have to get through to them and others. Componentize so some devs can specialize in editors and others can specialize in distribution. We can't all dominate the same world, being all things to all people. What a difference it would make if we worked together. " created="Mon, 23 Aug 2021 00:32:31 GMT"/>
						<outline text="No more shitty editors, lots of different kinds of editors for all kinds of writers. " created="Mon, 23 Aug 2021 00:35:16 GMT"/>
						<outline text="They wouldn't listen to me, but maybe they'll listen to a successful tech VC. :boom: " created="Mon, 23 Aug 2021 00:32:57 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="I wrote about this &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2021/04/06/150554.html?title=copypastetopublish&quot;&gt;problem&lt;/a&gt; with Substack earlier this year. " created="Mon, 23 Aug 2021 00:26:51 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Journalism is oblivious" created="Sun, 22 Aug 2021 15:43:37 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="Journalism says the pullout from Afghanistan was botched. Maybe so. Everything everyone does is botched, and that includes journalists, esp journalists, because no one is watching over them, reporting all their botchings. " created="Sun, 22 Aug 2021 15:43:50 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Journalism is oblivious to the past or future. Everything is in the moment. A lot like Trump in that way." created="Sun, 22 Aug 2021 15:44:12 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Why aren't the people obsessed with Afghanistan like journalism is? Because it was always there." created="Sun, 22 Aug 2021 15:45:44 GMT"/>
					<outline text="That Afghanistan is being botched isn't news, it's just that journalism has decided for now to pay attention to it. Next week it'll be something else. Always a horse race. Biden has to win or lose." created="Sun, 22 Aug 2021 15:44:31 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Never mind the context, we're still one election away from complete disaster. At least 49% of the people aren't overlooking this important fact." created="Sun, 22 Aug 2021 15:47:04 GMT"/>
					<outline text="In other words journalism is wrong." type="tweet" created="Sun Aug 22 15:43:14 +0000 2021" tweetId="1429469218433650707" tweetUserName="davewiner"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 21" created="Sat, 21 Aug 2021 15:31:05 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="21">
				<outline text="A hurricane is &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/accuweather/status/1429256151301074954&quot;&gt;coming our way&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hudson_Valley&quot;&gt;Hudson Valley&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Sun, 22 Aug 2021 01:38:05 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="I totally despised &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_White_Lotus&quot;&gt;White Lotus&lt;/a&gt; through the first four episodes, but having so much invested in it, and the hook in the first episode, got me to watch the last two episodes, which were actually pretty good except for one bit that I saw coming and averted my eyes it was so disgusting. And you know the way they left it there's definitely going to be a season 2. " created="Sat, 21 Aug 2021 22:22:06 GMT" type="outline" image="http://scripting.com/images/2021/08/21/capnCrunchBlueMapleSyrup.png" imageLink="https://www.amazon.com/Crunchs-Ocean-Maple-Syrup-Bottle/dp/B087QS8JKQ"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R706isyDrqI&quot;&gt;1984&lt;/a&gt; may not have been like &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nineteen_Eighty-Four&quot;&gt;1984&lt;/a&gt;, but 2021 sure is. " created="Sat, 21 Aug 2021 17:26:11 GMT" type="outline" urlvideo="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R706isyDrqI"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://2021.opml.org/#1629559392000&quot;&gt;Cleaning up&lt;/a&gt; after the &lt;a href=&quot;http://opml.org/&quot;&gt;opml.org&lt;/a&gt; renovation. " created="Sat, 21 Aug 2021 15:31:06 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="TV interview tech sucks" created="Sun, 22 Aug 2021 01:42:46 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="You know what Zuck should work on, getting a network together for people who are interviewed on TV, so the quality gets a huge upgrade, and make the UI dead simple. I can't believe none of the big tech companies see this opportunity. The quality is uniformly awful." created="Sun, 22 Aug 2021 01:42:54 GMT"/>
					<outline text="No one knows if people want to sit in virtual reality &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nbcboston.com/lx/facebook-wants-us-to-put-on-a-vr-headset-to-go-to-work-not-everyone-is-happy/2471118/&quot;&gt;conference rooms&lt;/a&gt;, but we know for sure that TV is built around a new way of discussion, and there's no prospect for this changing. So someone ought to capitalize on the vacuum." created="Sun, 22 Aug 2021 01:43:06 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 20" created="Fri, 20 Aug 2021 12:42:15 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="20">
				<outline text="No one cares what you think. " created="Fri, 20 Aug 2021 22:22:13 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="When you start a war, you better be prepared to win it. If you can't win, getting out is going to be ugly, no matter what. Because US journalism is pretending there's another way to get out, they make it necessary for the US to bend over and make more concessions to the Taliban" created="Fri, 20 Aug 2021 22:20:08 GMT" type="outline" image="http://scripting.com/images/2021/08/20/giJoe.png"/>
				<outline text="You know where [[Twitter]] asks &quot;What's happening?&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/images/2021/08/20/noOneCaresWhatYouThink.png&quot;&gt;This might work better&lt;/a&gt;. It's in the spirit of the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dTGfLObZYfU&quot;&gt;Progressive commercials&lt;/a&gt; where they teach people not to be their parents. &quot;The waiter does not need to know your name.&quot; Yet there are exceptions. There are a few people who write on Facebook who, when they write, I always stop and read. Because they have a track record of finding interesting things for me to think about. They write well too." created="Fri, 20 Aug 2021 14:15:20 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="A new feature in PagePark (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/pagePark#v0824-81721-by-dw&quot;&gt;v0.8.24&lt;/a&gt;) made it possible to use a custom template for &lt;a href=&quot;http://opml.org/&quot;&gt;opml.org&lt;/a&gt;. I wanted to put a menu at the top of the page, linking to other outlines on the site. " created="Fri, 20 Aug 2021 14:05:03 GMT" type="outline"/>
