					<outline text="Now back to the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/drummerTesting&quot;&gt;Drummer&lt;/a&gt; release. 😀" created="Fri, 20 Aug 2021 13:35:03 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Catching up on the news" created="Fri, 20 Aug 2021 14:59:32 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I caught up on the news last night, and was surprised to hear that somehow what's going on in Afghanistan is dooming the Biden presidency." created="Fri, 20 Aug 2021 14:59:37 GMT"/>
					<outline text="And the reporters, esp Wolf Blitzer, are spinning it that way through the words they use to characterize events. And as a result, everyone has to tiptoe in this space. It's a dangerous time. The whole thing could explode at any time. Beating the drum for war, as they are, is a crazy crazy thing to do, as destructive as invading the Capitol on January 6." created="Fri, 20 Aug 2021 14:59:56 GMT"/>
					<outline text="If they felt so strongly about Afghanistan (they didn't) why didn't they say something before? They had 20 years to speak up. No one ever did. Better to leave it to fester. Let's live this lie, everyone seemed to agree. Now all of a sudden, Afghanistan is more important as everything else.  " created="Fri, 20 Aug 2021 15:00:57 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Here's the thing, this all is fake news. It's worse than the lies on Facebook because they use brands like CNN and the NYT to lie this way." created="Fri, 20 Aug 2021 15:01:49 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 19" created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 12:21:31 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="19">
				<outline text="Silos vs open" created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 12:21:32 GMT" type="outline" description="It's easy to be part of a silo, impossible to be part of all of them. " metaImage="http://scripting.com/images/2021/08/19/silosHeader.png">
					<outline text="I love this quote about [[RSS]] in the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theverge.com/2021/8/18/22630517/apple-podcasts-subscriptions-launch-dashboard&quot;&gt;Vox piece&lt;/a&gt; about Apple and other bigco's trying to take over podcasting. " created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 12:21:36 GMT">
						<outline text="“The beauty of RSS was just publish it and it goes everywhere — it’s just there, and it’s available.” " created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 12:21:56 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="It says clearly what the faceoff is over." created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 12:23:05 GMT" flBulletedSubs="true">
						<outline text="It's easy to be part of a silo, impossible to be part of all of them. " created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 12:23:03 GMT"/>
						<outline text="In the open world, it's easy to be part of all of podcast players, but it's  harder to get started, you have to do more for yourself." created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 12:23:25 GMT"/>
						</outline>
					<outline text="Blogging went through the same thing that [[podcasting]] is going through now, it was taken apart by Twitter, Facebook, Google Reader, Medium and lately Substack. You couldn't write in one place and have your writing flow to all of them, the way podcasting works today. They don't agree on what a post is, so no matter what, you'd have to write at least two or three versions of a post. In the end, you just blow them all off, because it isn't worth the trouble and the resulting format is taking the fun out of your thinking and writing process. You aren't getting anything out of it. Not money, not exploration of ideas, not getting other people excited." created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 12:24:10 GMT"/>
					<outline text="There is a sweet spot, it's possible, but you can't wander into it, it has to be done consciously, with a shared vision among devs, or it can't work." created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 12:25:48 GMT"/>
					<outline text="One of the reasons I'm so excited about [[Tools for Thought]] is it's a chance to start something new, to use the open principles of established by blogging and podcasting, foster a community of developers, each of whom understand that they're part of an ecosystem, they are not themselves the whole ecosystem. That's the key idea that most developers have yet to embrace. It requires some maturity to understand this idea. " created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 12:26:14 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I wonder if any journalists covering the future of podcasting will even consider that it't more than a battleground for big companies." created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 12:27:15 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Edward Hopper" created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 12:44:12 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.wikiart.org/en/edward-hopper/ryders-house&quot;&gt;Ryder's House&lt;/a&gt;, 1933." created="Thu, 19 Aug 2021 12:44:16 GMT" inlineImage="http://scripting.com/images/2021/08/19/rydersHouse.png"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
